</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">EZ Bar Preacher Curl Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Sit on the preacher bench, with your chest against the pad and your arms fully extended over the bench.</li>



<li>Grip the EZ bar with an underhand grip, hands shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Curl the bar towards your shoulders, focusing on contracting your biceps at the top of the movement.</li>



<li>Slowly lower the bar back to the starting position, maintaining control throughout.</li>



<li>Repeat for the desired number of repetitions.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your upper arms stationary to isolate the biceps effectively.</li>



<li>Avoid locking your elbows at the bottom to maintain tension on the biceps.</li>



<li>Start with a moderate weight to perfect your form before increasing the load.</li>



<li>Hold the top position briefly to enhance peak contraction.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets &amp; Reps</h4>



